# Review · Knowledge base · Coverage

For every meaningful feature, fix, or behavior change in this repo, finish these three before calling the work done:

## 1. Code review (self-check)

- Tenant / license isolation, authz, and secrets (no `VITE_*` secrets)
- Offline Mobile: **never** upload or store ERP business data on our cloud
- Error paths, edge cases, and removal of dead APIs/UI you replaced
- Prefer small, focused diffs; match existing patterns

## 2. Engineering knowledge base

Update Engineering Academy (and related docs) when behavior changes:

- `engineering-academy/docs/` — API, deployment, architecture, security as relevant
- Manual cases under `tests/cases/` when human QA steps change
- Keep docs accurate (e.g. do not document removed cloud backup storage)

## 3. Coverage

- Add or update automated tests for the new behavior (API / unit)
- Update `tests/cases/*.md` for flows that stay manual
- Run the touched test files before finishing

If a change is docs-only or pure rename with no behavior change, skip tests but still fix stale knowledge-base pages that mention the old behavior.
